t those are usually more common in children as well, though they can occur in adults.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028639,0.05321,0.068901,0.081321,0.094217,0.10087,0.11124,0.11307,0.10739,0.096779,0.081444,0.062918],"unified_progress":[0.029195,0.05847,0.079984,0.094446,0.10158,0.11096,0.10809,0.10523,0.09915,0.094171,0.070429,0.048293]},{"section":10,"text":"Wait, another thought: could it be a ependymoma?","dimension":5,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023193,0.048144,0.067124,0.079943,0.092989,0.10254,0.1067,0.10998,0.10691,0.10892,0.086963,0.066584],"unified_progress":[0.031038,0.070427,0.08835,0.10162,0.10347,0.1007,0.10394,0.09955,0.093992,0.089444,0.070137,0.047331]},{"section":11,"text":"Ependymomas often occur in the cerebellum and can have a cystic component.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028691,0.052314,0.069604,0.083646,0.096591,0.10295,0.11273,0.11185,0.1054,0.094018,0.0789,0.063306],"unified_progress":[0.032225,0.063906,0.086119,0.10187,0.10722,0.11284,0.10698,0.10084,0.094558,0.081462,0.063553,0.048425]},{"section":12,"text":"They can also enhance with contrast.","dimension":12,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037436,0.053998,0.071188,0.083194,0.094466,0.10039,0.10603,0.10657,0.10415,0.094807,0.082626,0.065141],"unified_progress":[0.0434,0.068774,0.084128,0.093708,0.10097,0.10258,0.10074,0.099416,0.095518,0.090146,0.070374,0.050245]},{"section":13,"text":"The ataxia aligns with a cerebellar lesion, which fits with ependymomas.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032873,0.054853,0.071056,0.082206,0.091036,0.095737,0.10059,0.10118,0.099857,0.095528,0.090298,0.084783],"unified_progress":[0.034745,0.061953,0.078397,0.088584,0.094816,0.098739,0.097656,0.097293,0.096958,0.090907,0.083977,0.075974]},{"section":14,"text":"Alternatively, could it be a hemangioblastoma?","dimension":5,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,